<section xml:id="sec-introduction-to-data-analysis">
  <title>Introduction to Data Analysis</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section introduces the fundamental concepts of data analysis, providing a foundation for understanding how data can be used to answer questions and solve problems.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Understand what data analysis is and why it is important</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Learn about different types of data</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Explore the data analysis process</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-what-is-data-analysis">
    <title>What is Data Analysis?</title>
    <p>
      Data analysis is the process of inspecting, cleansing, transforming, and modelling data with the goal of discovering useful information, informing conclusions, and supporting decision-making.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-importance-of-data">
    <title>The Importance of Data</title>
    <p>
      In today's world, data is everywhere. Understanding how to work with data is an essential skill for making informed decisions in various fields.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
